Sentencas: La1-xSrxCo1-yFeyO3-delta perovskite materials have been considered as potential cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells operating at intermediate temperatures.
Titulo: Oxygen stoichiometries in La1-xSrxCo1-yFeyO3-δ perovskites at reduced oxygen partial pressures

Sentencas: The effect of temperature, ambient oxygen partial pressure and composition on the extent of oxygen deficiency was electrochemically investigated for various perovskites by means of solid electrolyte coulometry.
Titulo: Oxygen stoichiometries in La1-xSrxCo1-yFeyO3-δ perovskites at reduced oxygen partial pressures

Sentencas: Experiments were performed at reduced oxygen partial pressures between 1.3 X 10(-3) and 6 X 10(-5) atm since in a real fuel cell under cathodic bias, the material near the electrode/electrolyte interface is expected to be in a reduced state.
Titulo: Oxygen stoichiometries in La1-xSrxCo1-yFeyO3-δ perovskites at reduced oxygen partial pressures

Sentencas: It was found that the degree of oxygen non-stoichiometry (delta) increases with increasing temperature, decreasing oxygen partial pressure and increasing Sr or Co content.
Titulo: Oxygen stoichiometries in La1-xSrxCo1-yFeyO3-δ perovskites at reduced oxygen partial pressures

Sentencas: Transient re-equilibration experiments were also performed in an attempt to investigate the oxygen transport characteristics of the perovskite under various operating conditions.
Titulo: Oxygen stoichiometries in La1-xSrxCo1-yFeyO3-δ perovskites at reduced oxygen partial pressures

Sentencas: These experiments have shown that the time needed for re-equilibration increases with increasing oxygen deficiency.
Titulo: Oxygen stoichiometries in La1-xSrxCo1-yFeyO3-δ perovskites at reduced oxygen partial pressures
